      "content": "Your frustration is valid, but the feeling that our efforts are futile often comes from looking at the wrong scale—small actions like planting a tree or reducing waste actually do help, even if they don't stop the \"crash\" entirely. Engaging with the world feels pointless only if you believe the end result is guaranteed and unchangeable, which is a mindset that can lead to despair. Instead, shifting focus to what you can control might make the journey more bearable, even if the destination remains uncertain. Sometimes, simply trying to build something small, like a garden or a community, is the most powerful way to push back against the feeling of hopelessness.",
