      "content": "it just feels so hollow though. like if the house is on fire, why stay inside to try and plant flowers in the living room? it feels more honest to just accept that it's over. i look at the math and the projections and it just feels like the most rational thing is to not participate in a dying world. it feels like the only way to actually have some peace is to just... not be here for the end of it.",
